Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteIoFiller(25.10)                                    deleteIoFiller(25.10)

Name
       deleteIoFiller - Deletes I/O filler cell instances from the design

Syntax
        deleteIoFiller

       [-help]

       [-cell {<name_list>}]

       [-from <coord>]

       [-prefix <prefix>]

       [-ring <num>]

       [-side {top | bottom | left | right}]

       [-to <coord>]

       [-logic [-deriveConnectivity]]

       Deletes I/O filler cell instances from the design. Use this command af-
       ter filler cells have been added using the addIoFillercommand.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each deleteIoFiller parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man deleteIoFiller

       -cell {<name_list>}
              Specifies the name list of the I/O filler cells to be removed.

              Data_type: list, optional

       -deriveConnectivity
              Deletes connectivity for I/O fillers.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -from <coord>
              Specifies the coordinates of the starting  location  from  where
              I/O  filler  cells are to be removed. The values are in microme-
              ters.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -logic Deletes non-physical logical I/O filler cells created by the ad-
              dIoFiller command.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -prefix <prefix>
              Specifies the prefix of the names of I/O filler instances to  be
              removed.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -ring <num>
              Specifies the number of the ring from which I/O filler cells are
              to  be  removed.  Use  this  parameter if you want to delete I/O
              filler cell instances from only a specific I/O ring in a  multi-
              ple I/O ring design.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -side {top | bottom | left | right}
              Specifies  the  side  as  top  side, bottom side, left side, and
              right side of the I/O box from which the I/O filler cells are to
              be removed.

              Default: If you do not specify this  parameter,  all  sides  are
              specified.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -to coord
              Specifies  the coordinates of the ending location till which I/O
              filler cells are to be removed. The values are in micrometers.

              Data_type: float, optional

Related Information
              * addIoFiller

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

